This paper is about coreference resolution, which is a natural language processing task, so it is likely to belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) category. The paper also introduces a differentiable approximation and uses attention mechanisms, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, so it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The paper proposes a new model that improves accuracy while being more computationally efficient, which suggests it could belong to the cs.LG (Learning) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) categories. Finally, the paper uses a coarse-to-fine approach, which is a common technique in computer vision, so it could also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) category.
